node.text:
Introducing our new collection: Hokusai x Tsuki

Katsushika Hokusai (1760 – 1849), was an eccentric Japanese artist, ukiyo-e painter, and printmaker of the Edo period. Hokusai is best known for the woodblock print series Thirty-Six Views of Mount Fuji which includes the internationally iconic print The Great Wave off Kanagawa.

Tsuki has reimagined some of Hokusai’s most recognizable pieces, available now, as a very limited production run.

Pieces ship from the UK starting in early August.

Link in bio to shop!

node.text:
Introducing Tsuki X @Bagandbones 💗 One of our brightest collaborations to date! We’ve designed some very special lights, inspired by the Tsuki logo & Japanese Kanji for moon, with the @bagandbones team.

And it’s no coincidence that we are launching this on the eve of the “Super Flower Blood Moon” the biggest and brightest full moon of the year.

To celebrate the launch of the bag&bones Tsuki LED Neons we’re giving one lucky winner the chance to be the first to get their hands on a bag&bones Tsuki LED Neon.

Click the link in our bio to check them out. Make sure you like this post and follow @tsuki_market & @bagandbones for a chance to win one of these neon lights and tag a friend for an extra entry! Competition ends midnight 3rd June. The winner will be contacted within 3 days via Instagram DM. See www.bagandbones.co.uk for competition T&Cs.
